member.summary:
            According to interface protocol design (ItemTracking protocol and TCPServer2Client 
            protocol), there are 3 types of incoming messages:

ItemTracking message - Only come from Gateway-External communication chain. 
            E.g. come from PLC; 

BagEvent (BEV) message - Only come from Gateway-Internal communication chain;
            E.g. come from SAC SortEngine Service; 

Running Status Request (SRQ) and Reply (SRP) message - Only come from 
            Gateway-Internal communication chain. E.g. come from BHS Console Console Application;

Perform database initialization tasks:
1. Check database readiness by open DB connection to it. The opened DB connection will be closed immediately after it is opened;
2. Load system parameter settings from database table into global variables.
